article.headline: Austin Peay 80, Jacksonville St. 69
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. (AP) -- Anthony Davis scored 19 points to lead Austin Peay to an 80-69 win over Jacksonville State on Thursday. Davis hit 2-of-2 3-pointers for the Governors (8-13, 6-3 Ohio Valley Conference). Zac Schlader had 16 points and shot 8-of-11 from 3-point range. Todd Babington added 15 points, Maurice Hampton had 14 and William Durden had 12. The Governors led 37-29 at halftime. B.J. Spencer led the Gamecocks with a game-high 20 points. Walker Russell added 18 points, Tim Lewis had 15 and Anthony Wilson had 11. Austin Peay shot 66.6 percent from the field and the Gamecocks shot 48.0 percent.
